  <question type="stack">
    <name>
      <text>Finding the time and distance covered by two motorist travelling towards each other</text>
    </name>
    <questiontext format="moodle_auto_format">
      <text><![CDATA[<p>
A motorist left <strong>Nakuru</strong> for <strong>Nairobi</strong>, a distance of
{@D@} km, at {@t1_time_str@} am and travelled at an average speed of {@v1@} km/h.</p>
<p>Another motorist left <strong>Nairobi</strong> for <strong>Nakuru</strong> at {@t2_time_str@} am and travelled at {@v2@} km/h.
</p>

<p>Find:</p>
<ol type="a">
<li>The time they met:<br><br>\({@t2_time_str@}\,\, \text{am}+ \)[[input:ans1]] hours [[validation:ans1]] [[feedback:prt1]]</li>
<br>
<li>How far from Nairobi they met:<br><br> [[input:ans2]] km [[validation:ans2]] [[feedback:prt2]]</li>
</ol>]]></text>
    </questiontext>
    <generalfeedback format="moodle_auto_format">
      <text><![CDATA[<h3>Worked solution</h3>
<p>The first motorist starts earlier than the second. During the delay of
\({@delay_h@} \text{ hours}\) the first motorist travels: </p>
<p>\({@v1@} \text{km/h} \times {@delay_h@} \text{h} = {@d_headstart@} \text{ km}\)</p>
<p>When the second motorist starts, the remaining distance between them is:</p>
<p>\({@D@} \text{ km}  - {@d_headstart@} \text{ km} = {@d_remaining@} \text{ km}\)</p>
<p>Since the motorists are travelling towards each other, their Relative speed is:</p>
<p>\({@v1@} + {@v2@} = {@v_rel@} \text{ km/h}\)</p>
<p>The time taken from the second motoristâ€™s departure until they meet is:</p>
<p>\(\frac{{@d_remaining@}}{{@v_rel@}} = {@t_after_2@} \text{ hours}\)</p>
<p>Therefore, the time they is:</p>
<p>Second motorist's start time + {@ta1@} hours or first motorist's start time +{@delay_h + t_after_2@} hours </p>
<p>The distance from Nairobi is:</p>
<p>\({@v2@} \times {@t_after_2@} = {@ta2@} \text{ km}\)</p>]]></text>
    </generalfeedback>
